{"text": "Insectivore\nthumb|Entomophagy among animals: The giant anteater is a mammal specialized in eating insects\nEntomophagy is widespread among many animals, including non-human primates. Animals that feed primarily on insects are called insectivores.\n\nInsects, nematodes and fungi that obtain their nutrition from insects are sometimes termed entomophagous, especially in the context of biological control applications. These may also be more specifically classified into predators, parasites or parasitoids, while viruses, bacteria and fungi that grow on or inside insects may also be termed entomopathogenic (see also entomopathogenic fungi).", "embedding": [0.013616537, 0.06724817, -0.18448576, -0.0031556953, 0.036830947, 0.03082721, -0.09651507, -0.041381985, -0.032576215, 0.018704364, 0.03606111, 0.021884607, 0.09190141, 0.016533751, -0.02320128, -0.06976481, -0.021491809, -0.04774597, 0.054751847, 0.04465952, -0.021188412, 0.03797968, 0.06165507, -0.0024866492, 0.045667276, 0.004351685, -0.033688903, 0.015096444, 0.0033612608, 0.059561998, 0.016516361, -0.015224985, -0.008712769, 0.010093707, 0.015682064, 0.0036264204, 0.071600445, 0.02617104, 0.043343123, 0.01457261, -0.014125986, 0.0028732542, -0.0044706757, -0.06318993, -0.0138995955, 0.028389735, 0.04790816, 0.0022552693, 0.04471381, -0.08367496, 0.06958667, -0.04123387, -0.015658623, -0.021388508, 0.055629797, 0.034932967, 0.037036516, 0.0010903656, 0.026005916, -0.018555345, 0.0748609, 0.06786842, -0.06235074, 0.039880402, 0.016215174, -0.045514952, -0.027838703, 0.055162024, -0.018208826, -0.029142108, 0.045819998, -0.03815172, 0.030651428, 0.013428071, 0.012145755, -0.0027763792, -0.022375911, -0.0017687371, 0.017380692, 0.019320667, 0.042452, -0.002489352, 0.04048249, 0.024457773, 0.047499914, 0.00710797, -0.030396001, -0.028127281, 0.018087313, 0.06508942, 0.024024703, 0.029522154, 0.008103195, 0.011771664, -0.09855676, 0.010214165, -0.052424014, 0.009907865, -0.043445654, -0.018338094, -0.014535135